</p>

<p>In the night we went off to meet dad’s cousins Lucio (and Sandra) and Mario (and Lena) for dinner… The night was well wicked. It’s been a while since I’ve had a proper home cooked wog meal with all the crazy loud yelling across the table and at each other. I may not speak Italian but I picked up on a little of it. Had a bit of a chuckle at the loud “FUNGOULO” from Lucio to Mario!</p>

<p>The next day was much of the same, off to Prosecco for an amazing lunch with the same relatives as last night, plus their kids and Zia Valeria who reminds me ridiculous amounts of Nonna.</p>

<p>So incredibly happy I got to come to Trieste with the folks and meet the family.</p>

<p>Now back to London for RATM with Team Awesome.</p>

